{
  "text": "The thermodynamical model invokes complicated mechanisms in order to simulate adsorption of the chemical components. Without going into details (see [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] ), we merely recall the essential point which is to suppose the existence and uniqueness of a stable equilibrium state for the thermodynamical system of the two phases.",
  "correct_citation": {
